> ----- Original Message -----
> From: rvp999
> To: Type2_at_type2.co
> Sent: Sunday, March 11, 2001 12:41 PM
> Subject: Dipstick test
> 
> Hello,
> 
> I have read Muir regarding this test, but it is still not clear to me as to
> which part of the stick is applied to the test. The obvious answer is the
> top. Is this correct? Is there available a dip stick temp gauge for a 72
> 1700cc camper? Are they accurate? If not, is there a way to add degrees to
> the reading to get a reasonable accurate number?What is a safe running
> temperature? I cannot access the type2 site at all. Is the library still
> available?
> 
> Thanks
> 
> Rich Patano
> </pre>


